# GraphQL Partial Resolution Pattern

- Root resolvers map service results to `PartiallyResolved*` shapes (GraphQL scalar fields + the backend model object).
- Chained field resolvers hydrate related objects via request-scoped dataloaders on `GraphqlRequestContext` — never by re-querying per node.
- Keep the mapping explicit even when GraphQL and backend types look similar; each side must be able to evolve safely.

## Required flow

1. Service returns the domain model.
2. Root resolver maps to `PartiallyResolved*`.
3. Field resolver reads the relation key and calls `context.<x>Dataloader.load(...)`.

Exemplar: `Project.createdBy` in `firebase/functions/src/Graphql/Resolvers/Project/` hydrating via the user dataloader.

## When to use dataloader

- Use it for relation lookups across many nodes (avoids N+1 in connections).
- Skip it for one-off lookups where a single bounded service call already returns the data.
